messages.subject: Re: [AlwaysLearning] A virus was sent out
messages.msgSnippet: I didn t know that. I only knew that I had received it from a person on this group. I was certain it was accidental. But I thought others would want to know.
messages.messageBody:
I didn't know that. I only knew that I had received it from a person on this group. I was certain it was accidental. But I thought others would want to know.

But thank you for clearing that up.

Rebecca
----- Original Message -----
From: starsuncloud@...
To: AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Tuesday, April 30, 2002 2:07 PM
Subject: [AlwaysLearning] A virus was sent out


Rebecca,
The badtrans is usually a worm that dumps a backdoor Trojan into a file or
two.
It is primarily for the purpose of accessing your computer, so a hacker can
get personal info. It usually is not damaging, but depends on your system of
course.
Ren
